metadata.description: I had just moved to LA back in nov 2018 and in early 2019 I started seeing a therapist for the first time. a lot of the early work we did was spent dismantling the imposter syndrome I was feeling back then, and this demo became my mantra for that moment. writing it was like a grounding exercise that allowed me to settle into my reality and consider myself worthy of pursuing music full time. the lyrics still mean so much to me, and I'm sure one day here soon i'll find the right producer to really elevate it to a higher plane with. but for now I'm feeling called to share this version of it <3

lyrics.text:
fake it to make it
and fade in to wear out
i'm safe when i cave in
with nothing to care bout

cause sometimes i'm so surrounded
i spill my soul to roll around in
being lost is what i'm founded on

should i 
come to grips with my coming of age
or justify by "its just a phase"
i'm welcoming a change of pace

soon to be is new to me
whether tied in knots or unity
i feel at home
my skin and bones
better late than lucency
but these vivid dreams are killing me
honestly what good is gold?
when every night i live and die
way too young to feel this old

i can feel my wings
and all the little things again
whats searching for yourself
if you aren't even knee deep in it?

might burst into blames
can't hide behind the frames of reference
cause underneath everything
its all the same
its all the same

soon to be is new to me
whether tied in knots or unity
i feel at home
my skin and bones
better late than lucency
but these vivid dreams are killing me
honestly what good is gold?
when every night i live and die
way too young to feel this old

i'm being chased in my dreams
i'm being chased in my dreams again
